SIMPLE: wanion
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wanion
<hw>Wan"ion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably for OE.
<ets>waniand</ets> waning, p. pr. of <ets>wanien</ets>; hence, used of
the waning of the moon, supposed to be an unlucky time. See
<er>Wane</er>.]</ety> <def>A word of uncertain signification, used only
in the phrase <xex>with a wanion</xex>, apparently equivalent to
<xex>with a vengeance</xex>, <xex>with a plague</xex>, or <xex>with
misfortune</xex>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>B. Jonson.
Latimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wankle</ent>⟦br⟧
